Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly oil or spray a 13X9 inch pan with baking spray. Set aside. To make the cake: Place SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener, brown sugar, oil, egg substitute and pumpkin puree in a large mixing bowl. Mix until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Pour cake batter into prepared pan. Bake in preheated 350 degrees F oven 25-30 minutes or until when a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Cool cake. To make the frosting: Place frosting ingredients in a mixing bowl. Mix on medium speed until well blended. Ice cake when cake is completely cool. Optional garnishes: Sprinkle finely chopped walnuts or crushed ginger snaps over the top of the cake.